      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-GB 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">At 
        the request<span style="mso-tab-count: 1">&nbsp; </span>of the bishop 
        of Belley (France), in October 1863 the abbey of Aiguebelle sent forty-four 
        monks to make a foundation in the heart of the plateau of Dombes, 25 km 
        from Ars.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>O.L. of Dombes.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The monastery was erected to an abbey 
        on 29<sup>th</sup> January 1866.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-GB 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">In 
        1878, the community of Dombes numbered 118 members.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-GB 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">On 
        29<sup>th</sup> March 1880, a governmental decree bearing directly on 
        religious congregations was promulgated by the French State.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>It forbade their members to live together 
        or to wear the religious habit.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">6<sup>th</sup> 
        November 1880: the first expulsion from Dombes, by a detachment of gendarmes.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; 
        </span>The brothers dispersed.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Only 
        19 of them were allowed to remain in place.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; 
        </span>Some time after, however, the other monks returned.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>But the threat remained.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The abbot, Dom Ben</span></span><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">o�t, 
        then sought a place of eventual refuge outside the country.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>First in Italy, at San Martino (Cecina), 
        near Pisa, then in Spain (in the province of Guadalaxara, about 105 km 
        from Madrid).<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
