      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">The 
        monastery of Rajhenburg was placed under the patronage of Our Lady of 
        D�livrance, which was not altogether guileless, as that feast was normally 
        celebrated on 24<sup>th</sup> September.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; 
        </span>This transfer was certainly taken seriously, because within a few 
        years most of the monks became naturalised Austrians.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">On 
        15<sup>th</sup> December 1881, Dom Beno</span></span><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">�t 
        Margerand drew up the official document of foundation, which he dated 
        officially from 15<sup>th</sup> May 1881.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">23<sup>rd</sup> 
        March 1882: the second expulsion of the community of Dombes.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">On 
        10<sup>th</sup> September 1882 Dom Etienne, abbot of la Grande Trappe 
        and Vicar General of the Congregation, made the Regular Visitation of 
        the foundation in Styrie, and approved it.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">In 
        1889, Dombes again numbered 77 religious.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; 
        </span>O.L. of D�livrance was becoming prosperous and lay brother novices 
        were numerous.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Now they needed 
        a "monastic" enclosure and a church at this chateau-monastery.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The enclosure was established bit by bit.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; 
        </span>Happily for the beauty of the place, the project for a church did 
        not come to anything.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>They were content to build a bell-tower 
        on the roof of the chateau and to transform the former drawing room of 
        the chateau into a chapel for the choir, while the lay-brothers gathered 
        in another large and splendid room. <s><o:p></o:p></s></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">The 
        erection into an abbey took place on 10<sup>th</sup> September 1891.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The monastery was called, in German, "Kloster 
        Maria</span></span><span class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">-Erl�sung".<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>On the same day Dom Jean-Baptiste �palle 
        was elected abbot of the community.</span></span><span class=Bookman12Noir><span 
lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">1934: 
        For two years already the brothers of O.L. of D�livrance had been threatened 
        with takeover by the regime of Tito.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; 
        </span>They in turn sought a refuge in another country.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Mgr Roncalli, the nuncio in Bulgaria, 
        encouraged them to make a foundation in Sofia.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>But it was too costly.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>A priest from Algeria, on 
        retreat at Rajhenburg, suggested "Rivet", in the (?) area of Algeria. 
        The community numbered 81 monks.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">On 
        7<sup>th</sup> March five brothers went to see the place.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>So began the foundation of O.L. of Atlas.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">1939:<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The war between France and Germany !<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; 
        </span>In March 1941 the Germans besieged the monastery of O.L. of D�livrance 
        and expelled the monks.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The community took refuge in Bosnia, at 
        Marija-Zvijezda.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The two 
        communities lived side by side until the end of the war, and in 1945 the 
        Slovenian brothers went back to Rajhenburg.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">On 
        February 28, 1947, a new expulsion, this time by the communists.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The priest-monks "found new jobs" as parish 
        priests.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The brothers either 
        found employment or stayed in a parish in the entourage of one or other 
        of the priest-monks.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">Elected 
        abbot of Dombes in 1957, Dom Fran�ois Xavier Rouast did not rest until 
        he was granted the opportunity to visit our brothers of Rajhenburg (which 
        the communists had rebaptised Brestanica, from the name of the river which 
        runs through the village and flows into the Save there).<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Communism was relaxing and "tourists" 
        were allowed to enter Yugoslavia.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; 
        </span>And in fact the monks of O.L. of D�livrance were </span></span><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE"><span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></span></span><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">dispersed 
        through all the states of Yugoslavia: Slovenia, Croatia, Bosnia, Montenegro, 
        Macedonia, etc�<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">Dom 
        Xavier had been in direct contact with Dom Pius, abbot of Rajhenburg since 
        1940.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>He left in the spring 
        of 1960 to meet Dom Pius at the Italian-Slovenian border.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>From there, together, they visited the 
        dispersed brothers (still about forty of them).<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>In 1963 they attempted to reassemble the 
        community in a presbytery, in a magnificent location, at Radmirje.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>But the communal life lasted only for 
        a few years.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Each one went 
        back to his own place.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>From 
        then on, every year Dom Xavier undertook the "regular Visitation" of the 
        dispersed community.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>A trip 
        in a 2 CV </span></span><span class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">Citro�n, 
        taking several weeks! <o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">Becoming 
        abbot in 1990, Dom Bernard Christol fervently kept up this tradition.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Every year, first with Dom Xavier, then 
        with a German-speaking interpreter, he visited the remaining brothers.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Three brothers had found fraternal refuge 
        in the Cistercian abbey of Sticna (congregation of Mererhau) in the diocese 
        of Ljubljana.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Another had 
        found sanctuary in the Charterhouse of Pleterje.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>One brother remained as sacristan at the 
        shrine of O.L. of Lourdes at Brestanica, close to the chateau-monastery.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">In 
        1997, Dom Bernard was accompanied by M. Nicole, abbess of O.L. of La Gr�ce-Dieu, 
        "sister abbey" of O.L. of D�livrance through its filiation from Dombes.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>This visit brought great joy both to our 
        brothers and to the community of Sticna.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; 
        </span>M. Nicole was even received into the community refectory, at the 
        right of the abbot, Dom Anton Nadrah. The Abbey of Sticna was founded 
        in 1135 by Morimond, and so is </span></span><span class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">the</span></span><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE"> 
        older sister of Aiguebelle.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">In 
        1998, to mark the foundation and the restoration of C�teaux, Dom Bernard 
        invited Dom Anton to visit Dombes.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; 
        </span>As 1998 was also the centenary of the restoration of Sticna (1898), 
        this visit was put off until the following year.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; 
        </span>In spring of 1999, Dom Anton came to Dombes with Br Maximilien 
        and a family-brother of Sticna who speaks French well.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; 
        </span>They stayed for three days.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; 
        </span>We used the time to visit Ars, C�teaux, Gr�ce-Dieu, Acey, Aiguebelle, 
        Chambarand, Taiz�, Cluny and Paray-le Monial.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The fraternal bonds were deepened and, 
        one might say, extended!<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">But 
        the brothers of O.L. of D�livrance were dying out, one by one.<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Dom Anton, and then Dom Cassien, proposed 
        several times to the two brothers who were still at Sticna that they make 
        stability in that community, to be </span></span><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">an 
        integral part </span></span><span class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">"of" 
        that community.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>But the two 
        brothers wished to remain faithful to their Order, the Strict Observance.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">When 
        the dispersal of the community of Dombes was envisaged, in 2000 Dom Bernard 
        planned a new paternity for La Gr�ce-Dieu and for O.L. of D�livrance (there 
        was now only one remaining brother, Br Norbert, at Sticna,).<span 
style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The two communities opted for the paternity 
        of Acey.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Br. Norbert signed 
        his change of filiation for Acey on 15<sup>th</sup> September 2002,</span></span><span class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE"> 
        </span></span><span class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">the 
        feast of Our Lady of Sorrows and </span></span><span class=Bookman12Noir><span 
lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">the 
        patronal feast of Sticna.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">On 
        28<sup>th</sup> June 2004 Br Norbert, the last brother of O.L. of D�livrance, 
        died at Sticna.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>At the end 
        of August, Fr Bernard Christol and Dom Jean-Marc of Acey went to Sticna 
        and </span></span><span class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">to 
        the Chartreuse of </span></span><span class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">Pleterje 
        to thank these two sister communities for the fraternal care which they 
        had extended to our brothers.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Both 
        communities very kindly allowed us to celebrate </span></span><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">the 
        Divine Office with them </span></span><span class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">in 
        choir.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
class=Bookman12Noir><span lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE">But 
        henceforth O.L. of D�livrance does not exist any more!<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>
      <p class=MsoNormal style="TEXT-INDENT: 35.4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><span 
lang=EN-IE 
style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Arial'; mso-ansi-language: EN-IE"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
